    "body": "@Lenny222 I don't feel strongly either way but based on this comment about a different function in `os` I believe `path` is specifically for manipulating paths and that this makes more sense in `os`:\n\n```\n// NB: this is here rather than in path because it is a form of environment\n// querying; what it does depends on the process working directory, not just\n// the input paths.\n```\n",
